The paper presents a model of a recurrent neural network, which is a common topic in the field of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses optimization techniques and loss functions, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of state space viewpoint and vector Calculus of Variations suggests relevance to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as well. Finally, the paper mentions regression tracking of time-series, which is a common application in cs.CV (Computer Vision).
